				\begin{document}$$ \Delta M_{{{\text{DHA}},i}} = M_{{{\text{DHA}},i}} \cdot m \cdot \left( {T_{ 2,i\,} - \,{\text{T}}_{ 1,i} } \right), $$\end{document}ΔMDHA,i=MDHA,i·m·T2,i-T1,i,where m is the change in algal DHA content (%) per °C, which we obtained by modifying the linear regression of Hixson and Arts (2016) relating water temperature to algal DHA content. Full details of all terms in Eqs. 1 and 2 are available in the Supplementary Data File S2. We show ΣMDHA,i and ∆MDHA,i results for each of the four representative climate pathway (RCP) scenarios (i.e., RCP 2.6, 4.5, 6.0, 8.5) generated by the IPCC. These four scenarios give a range of water temperature increases and corresponding ΣMDHA,i and ∆MDHA,i results depending on human responses to limit climate change.
